## 🎯 Project Objective

As a Chartered Accountant and CISA working at the intersection of **finance, audit, and technology**, I recognized that understanding programming is no longer optional — it is essential for **automating repetitive tasks, analyzing data at scale, building audit tools, and understanding how systems work under the hood**. I completed Harvard University's **CS50P (Introduction to Programming with Python)** with a **perfect 100% score** — building a strong foundation in Python that I now apply to my professional work in audit, finance, and GRC.

> 💡 *"Most CAs don't deeply understand technology, and most IT professionals don't fully grasp finance. I work at their intersection — and Python is one of the bridges."*

